    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-09T15:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-09T15:45:00-05:00" n="616"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/2171: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-09T15:00:00-05:45"
                            >August 9, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:39 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. Department’s 80, August 8, 5 p.m. I appreciate the Department’s support in
                    the matter of the Guardia agreement. I hear [<hi rend="italic">hope?</hi>] you
                    may also induce the Nicaraguan Legation to cooperate in this matter. My
                    negotiations would be hindered if that Legation should transmit the Department’s
                    reply to Dr. Carazo in a form which would irritate President Moncada.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
